INTERVIEW QUESTIONS (With Answers)
Q1. What is the difference between a process and a thread?

Process → independent program
Thread → lightweight unit inside a process

Q2. How do you check CPU usage of a process?
top
ps aux --sort=-%cpu | head

Q3. What is a zombie process?

A process that finished execution but still has an entry in the process table.

Q4. How do you kill a process?
kill <PID>
kill -9 <PID>

Q5. How do you see all running services?
systemctl list-units --type=service

Q6. What is load average?

It shows the average number of processes waiting for CPU.

Q7. How to change priority of a running process?
renice 10 -p 2345

Q8. How do you find memory usage per process?
ps aux --sort=-%mem | head

Q9. What is the role of OOM-Killer?

Kills high-memory processes when RAM is full.
